My name isn’t Edward Waters, and I’m not seeing the office of Treasurer, but if I were, I’d use the Independent Herald to help spread my message. With a website audience that exceeds 50,000 visitors per month, and a social media audience that exceeds 20,000 followers across the Facebook, Instagram and Twitter platforms, the Independent Herald is the leading news content producer in Scott County.

If you want your ad to be seen by the voters who will decide Scott County’s August 4 general election, we have the audience you’re looking for. And our advertising packages include both responsive website banner ads that will look good on any device, as well as traditional ads in our e-edition, which remains popular — especially among our older readers.

But we aren’t willing to settle for delivering an audience. Your message will not be as effective as it could be if your design isn’t attractive. We help you design aesthetically-pleasing, eye-catching ad materials using cutting-edge graphic design techniques. If you don’t have a campaign website or Facebook page, we can provide web pages embedded on the ihoneida.com platform to help bring your message to voters. If you need help crafting announcements and news releases, we can provide assistance with those tasks, as well.

Get in touch with us today to get started developing your campaign with advertising rates that won’t drain your budget! Email ads@ihoneida.com for more information! Don’t delay! Premium spots are offered on a first-come, first-serve basis!
